<subSubSection pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="194.[151,1436,906,1473]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[267,516,1302,1329]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" pagination="1" refId="ref368514" refString="Rondani, C. (1859 b) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: III. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars secunda: Muscidae, Siphoninae et (partim) Tachininae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 243 + [1] p., 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1859">Rondani (1859b: 210)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[639,838,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="staegerii">
<emphasis box="[639,838,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">Metopia staegerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[199,285,1339,1365]" family="Number" pageId="194" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis box="[664,943,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">marem tantum observavi</emphasis>
[I observed only the male]”, received from R.C. Staeger. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T." box="[355,549,1374,1401]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" pagination="213 - 215" refId="ref362690" refString="Pape, T. (1985) The identity of Metopia staegeri Rondani, 1859 (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Entomologica Scandinavica, 16, 213 - 215. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631285 X 00081" type="journal article" year="1985">Pape (1985: 213)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<specimenCount box="[657,814,1375,1401]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
in the MZUF and designated a 
<typeStatus box="[1173,1276,1375,1401]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[1292,1314,1375,1401]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and 
<typeStatus box="[199,302,1411,1437]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195">paralectotype</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[318,341,1411,1437]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). Not included by him in the type series are an additional 
<specimenCount box="[984,1158,1411,1437]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
: 
<specimenCount box="[1168,1295,1411,1437]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="male">three males</specimenCount>
(all paralectotypes) belonging, in his opinion, to a different species, and 
<specimenCount box="[884,1007,1447,1473]" pageId="194" pageNumber="195" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
(non-type) because of its sex.
</paragraph>
